# Implementation checklist — {{PROJECT_NAME}}

Use before reporting a task complete.

## Read
- [ ] `CLAUDE.md` (especially Doc-code parity + Hard rules)
- [ ] `AGENTS.md`
- [ ] `docs/business/glossary.md` + the related business doc(s)
- [ ] Related use-case + repository contracts
- [ ] `docs/contracts/error-contract.md`, `docs/contracts/types-catalog.md`, `docs/contracts/code-style.md`
- [ ] `docs/testing/test-strategy.md`
- [ ] Related decision-table rows
- [ ] `docs/_generated/repo-map.md`

## Drift detection (do FIRST)
- [ ] Code and related docs are consistent.
- [ ] No leftover refs to renamed terms/routes/fields.
- [ ] If drift found → reported and waited for direction.

## Doc-code parity (8-step from `CLAUDE.md`)
- [ ] (1) User-visible behavior → business/UI doc updated.
- [ ] (2) Schema/persistence → `docs/database/**` + migration + tests.
- [ ] (3) Route/navigation → navigation-flow + route constants.
- [ ] (4) Core algorithm/rule → owning doc + decision table.
- [ ] (5) Rule/edge/validation → matching doc; no silent rule change.
- [ ] (6) New testable branch → decision row + test.
- [ ] (7) Status transition → `docs/business/system/overview.md`.
- [ ] (8) Old refs to old behavior → all fixed (`doc_guard terms`).

## WBS
- [ ] WBS row updated if affected, OR report states "WBS update: not needed — <reason>".
- [ ] Commit Traceability Log (§10) appended in the same commit.

## Verify
- [ ] `node tool/verify/run.mjs` (`--code` / `--docs`) → PASS (marker written).

## Review fan-out (code tasks)
- [ ] `code-reviewer` + `docs-drift-detector` run on the working-tree diff; blockers fixed.

## Report contains
- [ ] Files changed · Docs updated (+why) · Verify result · Subagent review · Drift detected.
